cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SE 

This paper proposes an extension of Concurrent Constraint Programming with a focus on time and soft constraints. As such, it is likely to be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the use of soft constraints and preference thresholds may also make it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the parallel and interleaved approaches to the language, which may make it relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
